    <p>Define a phase shift is the horizontal shift</p>
    <p>the phase shift is represented by the value 
      C
      C. A positive value of 
      C
      C indicates a shift to the right, and a negative value indicates a shift to the left.
      
      In simpler terms, a phase shift moves the entire graph of a trigonometric function horizontally, altering its starting position along the x-axis.</p>
